INSERT INTO `cm_article` VALUES ('8a3080d54c406b73014c510c6e9c0613', null, 'English News', null, '<p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">1.&nbsp;</span><u style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Consumer rights watchdog</u><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;CASE&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">(Consumers Association of Singapore)</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;is monitoring feedback on&nbsp;</span><u style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">potential profiteering</u><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;after the recent increase in&nbsp;</span><u style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">liquor duty</u><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;<u>announced as part of&nbsp;</u>this year\'s Budget.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><u>In extreme cases</u>, it says it would consider&nbsp;<u>naming the&nbsp;</u></span><u style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">errant</u><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><u>&nbsp;party</u>.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The&nbsp;<u>Finance Ministry</u>&nbsp;estimates that&nbsp;<u>the price of a bottle of beer</u>&nbsp;could&nbsp;<u>go up by</u>&nbsp;40 cents.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">All of these cases&nbsp;<u>involved</u>&nbsp;coffee shops&nbsp;<u>selling beer</u>. I think they shouldn\'t be&nbsp;<u>ripping us off</u>, just because the government has&nbsp;<u>proposed a hike</u>.I hope the government can&nbsp;<u>send some inspectors to</u>&nbsp;check all the coffee shops. Is the price raised reasonable?&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">CASE says it will&nbsp;<u>rely on</u>&nbsp;public feedback in deciding&nbsp;<u>whether or not</u>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<u>take action</u>, and if it discovers that&nbsp;<u>price hikes</u>&nbsp;are indeed too high, it will&nbsp;<u>investigate the reasons</u>&nbsp;for the increase thoroughly.I have to&nbsp;<u>change my signboards</u>.But where people have&nbsp;<u>taken advantage of</u>&nbsp;tax increases. For those who do not&nbsp;<u>respond to this engagement</u>, CASE will consider&nbsp;<u>adopting a name-and-shame policy</u>. It may also&nbsp;<u>publicise price information</u>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<u>nearby establishments</u>.&nbsp;<u>Send a signal</u>&nbsp;that consumers have choices and they will not accept prices that are&nbsp;<u>arbitrarily set</u>&nbsp;by people.&nbsp;<u>Meanwhile</u>,&nbsp;<u>supermarket chains</u>&nbsp;such as Fairprice and Sheng Siong say they are not&nbsp;<u>raising prices&nbsp;</u>yet, pending&nbsp;<u>further discussions</u>&nbsp;with suppliers.</span></p><p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">2.A teacher has been&nbsp;<u>sentenced to</u>&nbsp;26 months&nbsp;<u>in jail</u>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<u>having sex with</u>&nbsp;one of his students and&nbsp;<u>committing indecent acts with</u>&nbsp;another. Yeo Chang Yong&nbsp;<u>pleaded guilty to</u>&nbsp;having sex with a 15-year-old and&nbsp;<u>performing obscene acts</u>&nbsp;on a 14-year-old, these include&nbsp;<u>hugging and kissing</u>&nbsp;the student. The&nbsp;<u>district judge</u>&nbsp;says Yeo\'s conduct was&nbsp;<u>nothing short of&nbsp;</u>\"deplorable\" and stressed that he&nbsp;<u>broke the trust</u>&nbsp;<u>placed upon him as a teacher</u>.</span></p><p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. A new&nbsp;<u>phone scam</u>&nbsp;involving the hotline number of the&nbsp;<u>Immigration and Checkpoints Authority</u>, has&nbsp;<u>duped some members</u>&nbsp;of the public.&nbsp;<u>One victim</u>&nbsp;Mr Ragavendaran received a call telling him that he had&nbsp;<u>filled in</u>&nbsp;his birth date on his&nbsp;<u>immigration card</u>&nbsp;incorrectly.The caller&nbsp;<u>claimed to be from</u>&nbsp;the ICA, and asked him to pay $2,000 for&nbsp;<u>reprocessing charges</u>.&nbsp;<u>threatening to deport him</u>&nbsp;if he did not pay up.Mr Ragavendran did so, as the call&nbsp;<u>appeared to</u>&nbsp;be made from the ICA. This&nbsp;<u>scandal</u>&nbsp;will make use of voice-over Internet technology to&nbsp;<u>spoof</u>&nbsp;the incoming phone number, such that a different number would&nbsp;<u>appear on</u>&nbsp;the user\'s mobile phone. When the public&nbsp;<u>suspects that</u>&nbsp;the person on the other side is asking for too much information, they should&nbsp;<u>request to terminate</u>&nbsp;the phone call and instead&nbsp;<u>call back the other person</u>, so that they can verify that this person&nbsp;<u>is actually calling from</u>&nbsp;the organisation the claim to be calling from. The ICA says it does not make calls for funds transfers&nbsp;<u>pertaining to</u>&nbsp;immigration matters.</span></p><p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. The&nbsp;<u>contractor</u>&nbsp;<u>in charge of&nbsp;</u>building the Bugis Downtown Line MRT station has&nbsp;<u>been fined</u>&nbsp;$70,000&nbsp;<u>in relation to</u>&nbsp;an accident at the worksite two years ago.Two Chinese workers died and eight others were&nbsp;<u>injured</u>&nbsp;after&nbsp;<u>temporary scaffolding</u>&nbsp;used for the construction of a pedestrian link-way near the station collapsed. A representative for Soletanche Bachy-Koh Brothers today pleaded guilty to a charge of failing to take safety measures at the site.The contractor had failed to ensure that formwork structures were regularly inspected by a supervisor, or certified by a professional engineer.</span></p><p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5.Some $9.4 million has been&nbsp;<u>disbursed</u>&nbsp;under the&nbsp;<u>Community Integration Fund</u>. Since it was&nbsp;<u>set up</u>&nbsp;five years ago. The fund supports organisations in&nbsp;<u>implementing activities</u>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<u>promote integration</u>&nbsp;<u>among newcomers</u>&nbsp;in Singapore. Of the organisations that apply for the fund each year, about half are new. The&nbsp;<u>National Integration Council&nbsp;</u>says this singals interest in&nbsp;<u>ground-up initiatives</u>&nbsp;that&nbsp;<u>promote integration</u>.This is more than just&nbsp;<u>a gathering of friends</u>. It\'s a group&nbsp;<u>made up of&nbsp;</u>Singaporeans and newcomers to the country. They\'ve been brought together by&nbsp;<u>civic group</u>&nbsp;Connexions International. The group was set up two years ago by this couple who form their own experience as newcomers in the US, understood the importance of building bridges to fit in.Since it was formed, the group has&nbsp;<u>reached out to</u>&nbsp;at least 600 newcomers in Singapore. It\'s one of the 170 or so organisations that have benefited from the Community Integration Fund.The National Integration Council said that ground-up activities have helped new immigrations to&nbsp;<u>adapt better to</u>&nbsp;Singapore\'s&nbsp;<u>norms and culture</u>. as well as&nbsp;<u>foster understanding with</u>&nbsp;locals. .<u>A recent survey</u>&nbsp;of more than 4,000 Singaporeans&nbsp;<u>showed that</u>&nbsp;only&nbsp;<u>less than half</u>&nbsp;agreed or strongly agreed that the government has done well to&nbsp;<u>improve the integration of new immigrants</u>. 70% said it\'s the government\'s job to ensure&nbsp;<u>racial and religious harmony</u>&nbsp;in Singapore. It added that \"everyone&nbsp;<u>has a role to play</u>&nbsp;in integration\". All of us have&nbsp;<u>prejudices</u>&nbsp;and all of us have our own&nbsp;<u>preconceived ideas</u>&nbsp;and it is in the proccess of making friends of finding out more about other cultures that we&nbsp;<u>begin to debunk&nbsp;</u>some of these&nbsp;<u>myths and stereotypes</u>. Simply put, it\'s about&nbsp;<u>highlighting commonalities</u>, rather than differences.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">6.Among the&nbsp;<u>new bills</u>&nbsp;tabled in&nbsp;<u>Parliament</u>&nbsp;today was&nbsp;<u>one aimed at</u>&nbsp;giving better protection to victims of&nbsp;<u>cyber-bullying and stalking</u>.The Protection from&nbsp;<u>Harassment Bill&nbsp;</u>makes clear that as long as an act is&nbsp;<u>threatening</u>,&nbsp;<u>abusive</u>,&nbsp;<u>insulting</u>&nbsp;and causes&nbsp;<u>distress</u>&nbsp;to victims. it is&nbsp;<u>harassment</u>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<u>even if</u>&nbsp;it is done online. Under the new Bill, stalking which includes&nbsp;<u>loitering</u>&nbsp;near a victim\'s home, or messaging the victim everyday will be&nbsp;<u>criminalised</u>.The laws will also apply to acts committed outside Singapore. For example, when an offender who is overseas&nbsp;<u>stalks</u>&nbsp;a victim in Singapore and knows that the victim is in Singapore at the time of the offence.&nbsp;<u>Penalties</u>&nbsp;will be enhance to include&nbsp;<u>fine of up to $5000</u>, and&nbsp;<u>jail terms</u>.There will also be a wider range of remedies. For instance, the court can issue take-down notices to websites which publish offending material,&nbsp;<u>deemed as</u>&nbsp;harassment.Websites could also be directed to issue alerts to their readers over&nbsp;<u>falsehoods</u>&nbsp;made against victims.There are also Protection Orders that victims can apply for. And in urgent cases, they can ask for an&nbsp;<u>Expedited Protection Order</u>.</span></p><p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">7.The exact whereabouts and fate of Malaysia Airlines flight MH370&nbsp;<u>remain a mystery</u>. An official from MAS says the aircraft last made contact with air traffic controllers 120 nautical miles off the town of Kota Bahru on Malaysia\'s east coast. Search-and-rescue vessels have not seen signs of any&nbsp;<u>wreckage</u>.It has sent three&nbsp;<u>maritime enforcement ships</u>&nbsp;and a navy vessel backed by three helicoters Vietnam.There are 239 people on board, including 12&nbsp;<u>crew members</u>. Of those, 153 passengers, including an infant, are Chinese nationals.This is potentiallly the second fatal accident involving a Boeing 777 in less than a year.Angry relatives of the passengers are&nbsp;<u>accusing</u>&nbsp;the airline of keeping them in the dark.Chinese state media&nbsp;<u>criticised</u>&nbsp;Malaysia Airlines\' response to the situationA media scrum, as distraught family members were escorted into a conference room level two of Lido hoteldozens of volunteers are said to be attending to relatives of affected passengers, providing counselling.The face a barrage of camera crews and reporters.The Foreign Ministry and relevant diplomatic and consular missions of China have activated an emergency mechanism.It is convenient to express our deepest concern and solidarity with the people of Malaysia.we stand shoulder-to-shoulder with them.my sympathies immediately went to the families and loved ones of the passengers onboard,Prime Minister Najib appreciated our swift offer and response.We have already mobilised a RSAF(Republic of Singapore Air Force) C130.I offered further assistance of our submarine support-and-rescue vessel.People all over the world are rallying behind those who have loved ones on board flight MH370.</span></p><p style=\"line-height: 16.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">8. Authorities say&nbsp;<u>the failure of</u>&nbsp;<u>a security barrier</u>&nbsp;was the key reason why a driver&nbsp;<u>in a gold Mercedes-Benz</u>&nbsp;<u>managed to&nbsp;<b>breach</b></u>&nbsp;the Woodlands Checkpoint yesterday. He&nbsp;<u>drive off</u>&nbsp;even after the&nbsp;<b>tyres</b>&nbsp;of his car were&nbsp;<b>punctured</b>. The driver has been&nbsp;<b>arrested</b>, and four others are&nbsp;<u>assisting with</u>&nbsp;<b>investigations</b>.&nbsp;<u><b>Deputy</b>&nbsp;Prime Minister</u>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<u>Home Affairs</u>&nbsp;Teo Chee Hean says&nbsp;<u>measures to</u>&nbsp;make checkpoints more secure, an officer asked to search&nbsp;<u>the spare tyre compartment</u>. An officer&nbsp;<u>ran after</u>&nbsp;the car, but&nbsp;<u>fell and injured himself.</u>&nbsp;While&nbsp;<b>fleeing</b>, the driver&nbsp;<b>overtook</b>&nbsp;a moving car, went up the&nbsp;<b>curb</b>&nbsp;and then crashed through the security barrier that had already been activated. A video of&nbsp;<b>leaked</b>&nbsp;CCTV&nbsp;<b>footage</b>&nbsp;from the Causeway. An officer then&nbsp;<u><b>whips</b>&nbsp;out</u>&nbsp;his&nbsp;<b>baton</b>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<b>approaches</b>&nbsp;the driver\'s door.The driver manages to&nbsp;<u>dash through</u>&nbsp;the barrier. An&nbsp;<u>island-wide&nbsp;<b>manhunt</b></u>&nbsp;was&nbsp;<b>initiated</b>. The authorities recovered the abandoned vehicle. the incident&nbsp;<b>reinforces</b>&nbsp;<u>the findings of a review</u>.The alarm and barrier systems at the checkpoints are&nbsp;<b>inadequate</b>. you can have a situation whereby the car is loaded with ordinance. The police are investigating the driver for offences including&nbsp;<u>evasion</u>&nbsp;of customs&nbsp;<u>vandalism</u>&nbsp;and possibly&nbsp;<u>drug-related offences</u>.&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IQr-TnRiU10\" style=\"color: rgb(66, 139, 202); background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Youtube</a></p>', null, null, null, 'Language,English', null, '9999', 'en_SG', null, null, '2015-03-25 21:08:31', '2015-03-25 21:08:31', '0', '0', null, null);
